properties.name: spring.aop.auto
properties.description: Add @EnableAspectJAutoProxy.

properties.name: spring.aop.proxy-target-class
properties.description: Whether subclass-based (CGLIB) proxies are to be created (true), as opposed to standard Java interface-based proxies (false).

properties.name: spring.application.admin.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable admin features for the application.

properties.name: spring.application.admin.jmx-name
properties.description: JMX name of the application admin MBean.

properties.name: spring.autoconfigure.exclude
properties.description: Auto-configuration classes to exclude.

properties.name: spring.info.build.encoding
properties.description: File encoding.

properties.name: spring.info.build.location
properties.description: Location of the generated build-info.properties file.

properties.name: spring.info.git.encoding
properties.description: File encoding.

properties.name: spring.info.git.location
properties.description: Location of the generated git.properties file.

properties.name: spring.jmx.default-domain
properties.description: JMX domain name.

properties.name: spring.jmx.enabled
properties.description: Expose Spring's management beans to the JMX domain.

properties.name: spring.jmx.registration-policy
properties.description: JMX Registration policy.

properties.name: spring.jmx.server
properties.description: MBeanServer bean name.

properties.name: spring.jmx.unique-names
properties.description: Whether unique runtime object names should be ensured.

properties.name: spring.lifecycle.timeout-per-shutdown-phase
properties.description: Timeout for the shutdown of any phase (group of SmartLifecycle beans with the same 'phase' value).

properties.name: spring.messages.always-use-message-format
properties.description: Whether to always apply the MessageFormat rules, parsing even messages without arguments.

properties.name: spring.messages.basename
properties.description: List of basenames (essentially a fully-qualified classpath location), each following the ResourceBundle convention with relaxed support for slash based locations. If it doesn't contain a package qualifier (such as "org.mypackage"), it will be resolved from the classpath root.

properties.name: spring.messages.cache-duration
properties.description: Loaded resource bundle files cache duration. When not set, bundles are cached forever. If a duration suffix is not specified, seconds will be used.

properties.name: spring.messages.common-messages
properties.description: List of locale-independent property file resources containing common messages.

properties.name: spring.messages.encoding
properties.description: Message bundles encoding.

properties.name: spring.messages.fallback-to-system-locale
properties.description: Whether to fall back to the system Locale if no files for a specific Locale have been found. if this is turned off, the only fallback will be the default file (e.g. "messages.properties" for basename "messages").

properties.name: spring.messages.use-code-as-default-message
properties.description: Whether to use the message code as the default message instead of throwing a "NoSuchMessageException". Recommended during development only.

properties.name: spring.ssl.bundle.jks
properties.description: Java keystore SSL trust material.

properties.name: spring.ssl.bundle.pem
properties.description: PEM-encoded SSL trust material.

properties.name: spring.ssl.bundle.watch.file.quiet-period
properties.description: Quiet period, after which changes are detected.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.mode
properties.description: Determine when the task executor is to be created.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.pool.allow-core-thread-timeout
properties.description: Whether core threads are allowed to time out. This enables dynamic growing and shrinking of the pool. Doesn't have an effect if virtual threads are enabled.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.pool.core-size
properties.description: Core number of threads. Doesn't have an effect if virtual threads are enabled.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.pool.keep-alive
properties.description: Time limit for which threads may remain idle before being terminated. Doesn't have an effect if virtual threads are enabled.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.pool.max-size
properties.description: Maximum allowed number of threads. If tasks are filling up the queue, the pool can expand up to that size to accommodate the load. Ignored if the queue is unbounded. Doesn't have an effect if virtual threads are enabled.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.pool.queue-capacity
properties.description: Queue capacity. An unbounded capacity does not increase the pool and therefore ignores the "max-size" property. Doesn't have an effect if virtual threads are enabled.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.pool.shutdown.accept-tasks-after-context-close
properties.description: Whether to accept further tasks after the application context close phase has begun.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.shutdown.await-termination
properties.description: Whether the executor should wait for scheduled tasks to complete on shutdown.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.shutdown.await-termination-period
properties.description: Maximum time the executor should wait for remaining tasks to complete.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.simple.cancel-remaining-tasks-on-close
properties.description: Whether to cancel remaining tasks on close. Only recommended if threads are commonly expected to be stuck.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.simple.concurrency-limit
properties.description: Set the maximum number of parallel accesses allowed. -1 indicates no concurrency limit at all.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.simple.reject-tasks-when-limit-reached
properties.description: Whether to reject tasks when the concurrency limit has been reached.

properties.name: spring.task.execution.thread-name-prefix
properties.description: Prefix to use for the names of newly created threads.

properties.name: spring.task.scheduling.pool.size
properties.description: Maximum allowed number of threads. Doesn't have an effect if virtual threads are enabled.

properties.name: spring.task.scheduling.shutdown.await-termination
properties.description: Whether the executor should wait for scheduled tasks to complete on shutdown.

properties.name: spring.task.scheduling.shutdown.await-termination-period
properties.description: Maximum time the executor should wait for remaining tasks to complete.

properties.name: spring.task.scheduling.simple.concurrency-limit
properties.description: Set the maximum number of parallel accesses allowed. -1 indicates no concurrency limit at all.

properties.name: spring.task.scheduling.thread-name-prefix
properties.description: Prefix to use for the names of newly created threads.

properties.name: spring.threads.virtual.enabled
properties.description: Whether to use virtual threads.

properties.name: spring.web.error.include-binding-errors
properties.description: When to include "errors" attribute.

properties.name: spring.web.error.include-exception
properties.description: Include the "exception" attribute.

properties.name: spring.web.error.include-message
properties.description: When to include "message" attribute.

properties.name: spring.web.error.include-path
properties.description: When to include "path" attribute.

properties.name: spring.web.error.include-stacktrace
properties.description: When to include the "trace" attribute.

properties.name: spring.web.error.path
properties.description: Path of the error controller.

properties.name: spring.web.error.whitelabel.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable the default error page displayed in browsers in case of a server error.

properties.name: spring.web.locale
properties.description: Locale to use. By default, this locale is overridden by the "Accept-Language" header.

properties.name: spring.web.locale-resolver
properties.description: Define how the locale should be resolved.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.add-mappings
properties.description: Whether to enable default resource handling.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.cache-private
properties.description: Indicate that the response message is intended for a single user and must not be stored by a shared cache.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.cache-public
properties.description: Indicate that any cache may store the response.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.max-age
properties.description: Maximum time the response should be cached, in seconds if no duration suffix is not specified.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.must-revalidate
properties.description: Indicate that once it has become stale, a cache must not use the response without re-validating it with the server.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.no-cache
properties.description: Indicate that the cached response can be reused only if re-validated with the server.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.no-store
properties.description: Indicate to not cache the response in any case.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.no-transform
properties.description: Indicate intermediaries (caches and others) that they should not transform the response content.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.proxy-revalidate
properties.description: Same meaning as the "must-revalidate" directive, except that it does not apply to private caches.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.s-max-age
properties.description: Maximum time the response should be cached by shared caches, in seconds if no duration suffix is not specified.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.stale-if-error
properties.description: Maximum time the response may be used when errors are encountered, in seconds if no duration suffix is not specified.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.stale-while-revalidate
properties.description: Maximum time the response can be served after it becomes stale, in seconds if no duration suffix is not specified.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.period
properties.description: Cache period for the resources served by the resource handler. If a duration suffix is not specified, seconds will be used. Can be overridden by the 'spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol' properties.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.use-last-modified
properties.description: Whether we should use the "lastModified" metadata of the files in HTTP caching headers.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.cache
properties.description: Whether to enable caching in the Resource chain.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.compressed
properties.description: Whether to enable resolution of already compressed resources (gzip, brotli). Checks for a resource name with the '.gz' or '.br' file extensions.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable the Spring Resource Handling chain. By default, disabled unless at least one strategy has been enabled.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.strategy.content.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable the content Version Strategy.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.strategy.content.paths
properties.description: List of patterns to apply to the content Version Strategy.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.strategy.fixed.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable the fixed Version Strategy.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.strategy.fixed.paths
properties.description: List of patterns to apply to the fixed Version Strategy.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.strategy.fixed.version
properties.description: Version string to use for the fixed Version Strategy.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.static-locations
properties.description: Locations of static resources. Defaults to classpath:[/META-INF/resources/, /resources/, /static/, /public/].

properties.name: spring.git.properties
properties.description: Resource reference to a generated git info properties file.
